object.script:
tilt = 0 rollAngle = 0 vertCheck = true lineDist = property.getNumber('Degrees per Line') pixPerDegree = property.getNumber('Pixels per Degree') maxLineWidth = property.getNumber('Maximum Line Length as Screen Percent') lineDivideFactor = (property.getNumber('Minimum Line Length as Percent of Max')+1)*90 if property.getBool('Vertical Flip') then yMod = -1 else yMod = 1 end
function onTick() tilt = input.getNumber(1)*360 -- Tilt (Forward tilt sensor) supplied through composite 1 maxAngle = 90-math.abs(tilt) rollAngle = (input.getNumber(2)*360)/maxAngle*90 -- Roll (Right tilt sensor) supplied through composite 2 vertCheck = input.getNumber(3)>=0 if not vertCheck then -- Vertical check (Up tilt sensor) supplied through composite 3 tilt = tilt*-1 rollAngle = rollAngle*-1 end end
function calcXY(x,y,bearing,distance) bearing = math.rad(bearing + 90) y = y+math.cos(bearing) * -distance x = x+math.sin(bearing) * distance return x,y end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight()
if vertCheck then screen.setColor(100, 50, 0) else screen.setColor(50,50,255) end for lineAngle = -90, 90, lineDist do if lineAngle>0 and vertCheck then screen.setColor(50,50,255) elseif lineAngle>0 and not vertCheck then screen.setColor(100,50,0) end lineLen = (maxLineWidth*w)*(1-math.abs(lineAngle)/lineDivideFactor) currentY = (tilt-lineAngle)*pixPerDegree*yMod mX, mY = calcXY(w/2,h/2,rollAngle+90,currentY) lX, lY = calcXY(mX,mY,rollAngle,lineLen/2) rX, rY = calcXY(mX,mY,rollAngle+180,lineLen/2) screen.drawLine(lX,lY,rX,rY) end centerY = h/2+tilt*pixPerDegree*yMod screen.setColor(125,125,125) mX, mY = calcXY(w/2,h/2,rollAngle+90,tilt*pixPerDegree*yMod) lX, lY = calcXY(mX,mY,rollAngle,100) rX, rY = calcXY(mX,mY,rollAngle+180,100) screen.drawLine(lX,lY,rX,rY) screen.setColor(255,0,0) screen.drawRectF(w/2-1,h/2,2,2) end

object.script:
--customizible colors. you may edit them as you like.
--text color r1, g1, b1 = 155, 155, 155
--warning color r2, g2, b2 = 155, 155, 0
--bg color r3, g3, b3 = 0, 0, 0
--main code--
scr = screen imp = property.getBool("Measurements") function onTick() f = input.getNumber(1) s = input.getNumber(2) d = (input.getNumber(3))*-1 m = input.getNumber(4) end
function rd(num, dec) if dec > 0 then local mult = 10^(dec or 0) return math.floor(num * mult + 0.5) / mult else return math.floor(num) end end
function onDraw() scr.setColor(r3,g3,b3) scr.drawRectF(0,0,40,40)
--percentage perc = rd((f/m)*100, 1) if perc < 10 then scr.setColor(r2, g2, b2) else scr.setColor(r1, g1, b1) end scr.drawTextBox(1, 0, 32, 7, tostring(perc)..'%', 0, 0)
--consumpt scr.setColor(r1, g1, b1)
if imp then --imperial if d*60 < 0 then scr.drawTextBox(1, 8, 32, 7, 'Fills', 0, 0) elseif d*60*0.264 < 10 then scr.drawTextBox(1, 8, 32, 7, tostring(rd(d*60*0.264, 1))..'g/m', 0, 0) elseif d*60*0.264 < 1000 then scr.drawTextBox(1, 8, 32, 7, tostring(rd(d*60*0.264, 0))..'g/m', 0, 0) else scr.drawTextBox(1, 8, 32, 7, tostring(rd(d*0.06*0.264, 0))..'tg/m', 0, 0) end else --metric if d*60 < 0 then scr.drawTextBox(1, 8, 32, 7, 'Fills', 0, 0) elseif d*60 < 10 then scr.drawTextBox(1, 8, 32, 7, tostring(rd(d*60, 1))..'l/m', 0, 0) elseif d*60 < 1000 then scr.drawTextBox(1, 8, 32, 7, tostring(rd(d*60, 0))..'l/m', 0, 0) else scr.drawTextBox(1, 8, 32, 7, tostring(rd(d*0.06, 0))..'kl/m', 0, 0) end end --uptime if d*60 > 0 then uptime = f/(d*60) else uptime = (m-f)/(d*-60) end
if uptime > 0 and uptime < 59940 then if uptime > 30 then scr.setColor(r1, g1, b1) elseif d*60 > 0 then scr.setColor(r2, g2, b2) end if uptime <= 2 then scr.drawTextBox(1, 16, 32, 7, tostring(rd(uptime*60,0))..'s', 0, 0) elseif uptime < 100 then scr.drawTextBox(1, 16, 32, 7, tostring(rd(uptime,0))..'m', 0, 0) elseif uptime < 600 then scr.drawTextBox(1, 16, 32, 7, tostring(rd(uptime/60, 1))..'hrs', 0, 0) else scr.drawTextBox(1, 16, 32, 7, tostring(rd(uptime/60, 0))..'hrs', 0, 0) end else scr.drawTextBox(1, 16, 32, 7, '- m', 0, 0) end
--range if imp then ms = 'mi' range = rd(s*60/1000*uptime*0.6215, 0) else ms = 'km' range = rd(s*60/1000*uptime, 0) end
if range > 0 then if range > 10 then scr.setColor(r1, g1, b1) else scr.setColor(r2, g2, b2) end if range < 10000 then scr.drawTextBox(1, 24, 32, 7, tostring(range)..ms, 0, 0) elseif range < 100000 then scr.drawTextBox(1, 24, 32, 7, 'far', 0, 0) else scr.drawTextBox(1, 24, 32, 7, '- '..ms, 0, 0) end else scr.setColor(r1, g1, b1) scr.drawTextBox(1, 24, 32, 7, '- '..ms, 0, 0) end end

object.script:
si=math.sin co=math.cos pi=math.pi pi2=pi*2 s=screen ip=input
mx=gpsx my=gpsy zoom=1.5 zoomScale=zoom+zoom focusZone=false grid=250
function onTick() rx=ip.getNumber(1) ry=ip.getNumber(2) inputX=ip.getNumber(3) inputY=ip.getNumber(4) pressed=ip.getBool(1) and not isPressed--pulse isPressed=ip.getBool(1)
gpsx=ip.getNumber(10) gpsy=ip.getNumber(11)
compass=ip.getNumber(12)*pi2*-1 alt=ip.getNumber(13) if alt<0 then alt=0 end
zoomingIn=isPressed and iPIR(inputX,inputY,0,ry/5,6,ry/5) zoomingOut=isPressed and iPIR(inputX,inputY,0,ry/5*2,6,ry/5) reset=isPressed and iPIR(inputX,inputY,0,ry/5*3,6,ry/5)
if reset then focusZone=false zoom=1.5 grid=250 end if isPressed and inputX>6 then focusZone=true end if focusZone then if pressed and inputX>6 then tx,ty=map.screenToMap(mx,my,zoom,rx,ry,inputX,inputY) end cx,cy=map.screenToMap(mx,my,zoom,rx,ry,rx/2,ry/2) mx=cx+((tx-cx)*0.05) my=cy+((ty-cy)*0.05) else mx=gpsx my=gpsy end if zoomingIn and zoom>0.1 then zoomScale=zoom+zoom zoom=zoom-(zoomScale/100) end if zoomingOut and zoom<50 then zoomScale=zoom+zoom zoom=zoom+(zoomScale/100) end if zoom>0 and zoom<0.2 then grid=25 end if zoom>0.2 and zoom<0.5 then grid=50 end if zoom>0.5 and zoom<1 then grid=100 end if zoom>1 and zoom<2 then grid=250 end if zoom>2 and zoom<5 then grid=500 end if zoom>5 and zoom<10 then grid=1000 end if zoom>10 and zoom<20 then grid=2000 end if zoom>20 and zoom<40 then grid=4000 end if zoom>40 then grid=8000 end end function onDraw() w=s.getWidth() h=s.getHeight()
s.drawMap(mx,my+alt,zoom) s.setMapColorOcean(10,10,10) s.setMapColorShallows(15,15,15) s.setMapColorLand(50,50,50) s.setMapColorGrass(70,70,70) s.setMapColorSand(60,60,60) s.setMapColorSnow(60,60,60)
x1,y1=map.screenToMap(mx,my+alt,zoom,w,h,0,0) x2,y2=map.screenToMap(mx,my+alt,zoom,w,h,w,h) x1=math.floor(x1/grid)*grid y1=math.floor(y1/grid)*grid
s.setColor(0,0,0,20) for xx=x1,x2,grid do x,y = map.mapToScreen(mx,my+alt,zoom,w,h,xx,y1) screen.drawLine(x,0,x,h) end for yy=y1,y2,-grid do x,y = map.mapToScreen(mx,my+alt,zoom,w,h,x1,yy) screen.drawLine(0,y,w,y) end
dpsx,dpsy=map.mapToScreen(mx,my+alt,zoom,w,h,gpsx,gpsy) dpx,dpy=map.mapToScreen(mx,my,zoom,w,h,gpsx,gpsy) s.setColor(0,0,0,150) drawPointer(dpsx,dpsy+1,10,compass)--shadow s.setColor(255,255,255,60) s.drawLine(dpsx,dpsy,dpx,dpy)--line s.setColor(255,255,255) drawPointer(dpx,dpy,10,compass)
s.setColor(0,0,0,150) s.drawRectF(0,h/5,6,h/5*3)
if zoomingIn then s.setColor(255,255,255) else s.setColor(255,255,255,20)end s.drawTextBox(1,h/5,4,h/5,"+",0,0) if zoomingOut then s.setColor(255,255,255) else s.setColor(255,255,255,20)end s.drawTextBox(1,h/5*2,4,h/5,"-",0,0) if reset then s.setColor(255,255,255) else s.setColor(255,255,255,20)end s.drawTextBox(1,h/5*3,4,h/5,"r",0,0)
if not focusZone then if w>100 then s.setColor(0,0,0,150) s.drawLine(dpsx-6,dpsy-5,dpsx-10,dpsy-9) s.drawLine(dpsx+6,dpsy-5,dpsx+10,dpsy-9) s.drawLine(dpsx+6,dpsy+6,dpsx+10,dpsy+10) s.drawLine(dpsx-6,dpsy+6,dpsx-10,dpsy+10) s.setColor(255,255,255) s.drawLine(w/2-6,h/2-6,w/2-10,h/2-10) s.drawLine(w/2+6,h/2-6,w/2+10,h/2-10) s.drawLine(w/2+6,h/2+5,w/2+10,h/2+9) s.drawLine(w/2-6,h/2+5,w/2-10,h/2+9) end else x=dpx y=dpy L=h/6 s.setColor(255,255,255) s.drawRectF(w/2,h/2,1,1) if not iPIR(x,y,0,0,w,h) then x,y = w/2-x,h/2-y v = math.sqrt((x^2)+(y^2)) x,y = x/v,y/v s.drawLine(w/2-x*2,h/2-y*2-1,w/2-x*L,h/2-y*L-1) end end
s.setColor(255,255,255,30) s.drawRect(6,0,w-7,h-1) end
function iPIR(x,y,rX,rY,rW,rH) return x>rX and y>rY and x<rX+rW and y<rY+rH end function drawPointer(x,y,s,r,...) a=... a=(a or 30)*pi/360 x=x+s/2*si(r) y=y-s/2*co(r) screen.drawTriangleF(x,y,x-s*si(r+a),y+s*co(r+a),x-s*si(r-a),y+s*co(r-a)) end
